body:
@fkiraly and @AngelPone outside of the forecast combination case, I could see it being useful to be able to expect the residuals from a model. For example, to see if they have a clear pattern (suggesting the model doesn't fit well) or run a statistical test on them (e.g. are they normally distributed in the case of models like Arima that make this assumption).

Adding a convenience method seems straight-forward (but I could be missing something) -- something like:

```python
class BaseForecaster(BaseEstimator):
    def insample_residuals(self):
        self.check_is_fitted()
        if self.get_tag("requires-fh-in-fit", False):
             # Not sure if we should use `_fit` or `fit` here
             # Maybe `_fit` since it doesn't override the stored `fh`?
            return self._fit(self._y, fh=self._y.index).predict()
        else:
            return self.predict(fh=self._y.index)
```
